Durban - A truck was set on fire and at least two others looted of goods on the N2 between Hluhluwe and Mtubatuba in KwaZulu-Natal as protests turned violent on Tuesday. Videos doing the rounds on social media on Tuesday show people ripping open at least two and looting it of its goods. The KZN Road Traffic Inspectorate (RTI) said the road had been closed off in the Msekayi area. According to reports on Facebook, the protest is a result an industrial action by workers in the area. It was unclear what the protests were about on Tuesday morning. The Facebook page of Junior Jack Transport Having Handsome Drivers said: “Be warned and careful guys, trucks are burning between Hluhluwe and Mtubatuba.N2 closed as well as Mooi river”  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
