    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. “According to our officers at the scene one truck has been torched. For now, the road remains closed. As to the criminality of the matter, the SAPS will have to be contacted with regards to that,” she said. Police spokesperson, Thembeka Mbele said about 100 people were protesting. "Police from the area are at the scene, monitoring the situation and dispersing protestors," she said. Motorists were advised to avoid or delay travel to this area and to use alternate routes. Daily News